<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151903>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Miturgopelma australiensis (Hickman, 1944) comb. nov., male lectotype, AM KS6628: a, b, male palpal tibia, cymbium and bulb, ventral (a) and dorsal (b) views; female paralectotype, AM KS6629: c, epigyne, ventral view; d, female internal genitalia, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151903/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151905>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Miturgopelma baehrae sp. nov., male holotype, WAM T138016: a–c, male palpal tibia, cymbium and bulb, ventral (a, arrow shows embolus origin); and retrolateral (b, c) views (c, arrow shows unsclerotised basal zone of RTA); d, habitus, dorsal view. Images of palp by B. Baehr." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151905/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151957>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33. Miturgopelma ferruginea (L. Koch, 1873), comb. nov., male: a–e, QM S98250. a, e, palpal tibia, cymbium and bulb, ventral (a) and retrolateral (e) views; b, median apophysis, ventral view; c, d, habitus, dorsal (c) and ventral (d) views; e, retrolateral view; f, male holotype, RMS, RTA, retrolateral view showing bifurcate tip. Images of palp by B. Baehr." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151957/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

